<TITLE> BFF officials have punctuality problems </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com)  To protest failure of Bangladesh Football Federation officials to stick to press conference schedules, sports reporters Thursday boycotted a press conference to announce the preliminary squad for October's Mardeka Cup in Malaysia. The press conference was scheduled to start at 12.00pm, but some 25 reporters came out of the BFF conference room having found no BFF official despite being there for 15 minutes. BFF failure to start scheduled press conferences on time is a common phenomenon and its regular apologies after the repeated delays that usually last 30 minutes to one hour, prompted the reporters to take the decision for the first time. 
